
<div class="panel-group" id="accordion2">
  <div class="panel panel-default">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <h4 class="panel-title">
        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThirty">Who, What, When, Where, Why, How</a>
      </h4>
    </div>
    <div id="collapseThirty" class="panel-collapse collapse in">
      <div class="panel-body">
        <h4 class="headerunderline">Who</h4>
        <p>Unlimited amount of play may enter the 1v1 tournament of the AD2L</p>
        <h4 class="headerunderline">What</h4>
        <p>The AD2L (1v1) - Only Mid</p>
        <h4 class="headerunderline">When</h4>
        <p>EU: 21 MAY, @9.00 CEST</p>
        <p>NA/SA: 21 MAY, @7:30pm EDT</p>
        <h4 class="headerunderline">Where</h4>
        <p>Check-in on the Steam Group Chat 15 minutes before start (see above for start time). <%=link_to "Boycey", "players/1615"%>, <%=link_to "Trenza", "players/4745"%> or <%=link_to "Affinity", "players/140"%> will be in the steam group chat to assist you.</p>
        <h4 class="headerunderline">Why</h4>
        <p>For those of us not as good as DK, we play amateur tournaments.</p>
        <h4 class="headerunderline">How</h4>
        <ol>
          <li>1. Register from your teampage or <%=link_to "here", "register"%>.  (Can be found from the <%=link_to "My Info", (@current_user ? @current_user : "players/new")%>)</li>
          <li>2. Check-in 15 minutes before the tournament from the 1v1 tab <%=link_to "here", seasons_path%>. </li>
          <li>3. Use the <%=link_to "steam group chat", "steam://friends/joinchat/103582791435143521"%> to find your opponent</li>
            <ol class="sublist">
              <li>a. For example, if I’m listed on the bracket as Affinity, and my opponent is A3P, I’ll type into the chat: “Affinity vs A3P, join lobby ad2l123”/li>
              <li>b. As a general rule, ask for a caster if you want your game on Dota TV (ticketed). Casters might be calling your team, if so, go join their lobby!</li>
            </ol>
          <li>4. The winner will type into the chat (or steam msg <%=link_to "Affinity", "players/140"%>) they won their game. </li>
          <li>5. Rinse and repeat steps 2-4 until the 1st place is yours!</li>
        <ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
